aVBut when I looked at them,
p90
aVI didn't see any SS-like uniforms,
p91
aVswastika-like symbols on the wall,
p92
aVSieg Heil salutes \u2014
p93
aVnone of that.
p94
aVWhat I found instead
p95
aVwere people parading as respectable academics.
p96
aa(lp97
VWhat did they have?
p98
aVThey had an institute.
p99
aVAn "Institute for Historical Review."
p100
aVThey had a journal \u2014 a slick journal \u2014
p101
aVa "Journal of Historical Review."
p102
aVOne filled with papers \u2014
p103
aVfootnote-laden papers.
p104
aVAnd they had a new name.
p105
aVNot neo-Nazis,
p106
aVnot anti-Semites \u2014
p107
aVrevisionists.
p108
aVThey said, "We are revisionists.
p109
aVWe are out to do one thing:
p110
aVto revise mistakes in history."
p111
aVBut all you had to do was go one inch below the surface,
p112
aVand what did you find there?
p113
aVThe same adulation of Hitler,
p114
aVpraise of the Third Reich,
p115
aVanti-Semitism, racism, prejudice.
p116
aVThis is what intrigued me.
p117
aVIt was anti-Semitism, racism, prejudice, parading as rational discourse.
