aVHe hadn't always been a Holocaust denier,
p161
aVbut in the late '80s,
p162
aVhe embraced it with great vigor.
p163
aa(lp164
VThe reason I laughed also was this was a man
p165
aVwho not only was a Holocaust denier,
p166
aVbut seemed quite proud of it.
p167
aVHere was a man \u2014 and I quote \u2014
p168
aVwho said, "I'm going to sink the battleship Auschwitz."
p169
aVHere was a man
p170
aVwho pointed to the number tattooed on a survivor's arm and said,
p171
aV"How much money have you made
p172
aVfrom having that number tattooed on your arm?"
p173
aVHere was a man who said,
p174
aV"More people died in Senator Kennedy's car
p175
aVat Chappaquiddick
p176
aVthan died in gas chambers at Auschwitz."
